The '''Ministry of Health and Population''' is a [[Government of Nepal|governmental body]] of [[Nepal]] in charge of regulating the healthcare system and its implementation. The ministries tasks are manifold and include managing the development of the healthcare in Nepal, overseeing population policies, planning and implementation and overseeing [[List of non-governmental organizations in Nepal|non-governmental]] associated with health services in Nepal.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mohp.gov.np/english/function/mohp.php |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-11-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224103401/http://www.mohp.gov.np/english/function/mohp.php |archivedate=2013-12-24 |df= }}</ref>
== Heath care facilities == The Ministry of Health and Population runs and oversees all public hospitals in Nepal. These include four Regional Hospitals,<ref>{{cite web |title=Regional Hospitals |url=http://www.mohp.gov.np/content/regional-hospitals |publisher=Ministry of Health & Population |accessdate=1 September 2018}}</ref> 11 Zonal Hospitals,<ref>{{cite web |title=Zonal Hospitals |url=http://www.mohp.gov.np/content/zonal-hospitals |publisher=Ministry of Health & Population |accessdate=1 September 2018}}</ref> five [[Teaching hospital]]s,<ref>{{cite web |title=Teaching Hospitals |url=http://www.mohp.gov.np/content/teaching-hospitals |publisher=Ministry of Health & Population |accessdate=1 September 2018}}</ref> as well as district hospitals and general hospitals.
==Organisational Structure== The Department of Health Services serves under the ministry to facilitate and implement its work, mainly deliver health services and to maintain public hospitals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Department of Health Services |url=http://mohp.gov.np/content/department-of-health-services |publisher=Ministry of Health & Population |accessdate=1 September 2018}}</ref> Furthermore, two other departments also work under and with the ministry: * [[Ayurveda#Other countries on the Indian subcontinent|Department of Ayurveda]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Department of Ayurveda |publisher=Ministry of Health & Population |accessdate=1 September 2018}}</ref> * Department of Drug Administration (established 1979)<ref>{{cite web |title=Department of Drug Administration |url=http://mohp.gov.np/content/department-of-drug-administration |publisher=Ministry of Health & Population |accessdate=1 September 2018}}</ref>
